nl.tue.geometrycore.datastructures.priorityqueue

Class IndexedPriorityQueue<T extends Indexable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.geometrycore.datastructures.priorityqueue.IndexedPriorityQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class of objects stored in the priority queue

    public class IndexedPriorityQueue<T extends Indexable>
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides a priority queue on a custom comparator using indexable items. By using indexation, some methods can be done more efficiently. The ordering is based on a comparator. The smallest value according to this comparator is treated as the highest priority. Implementation partially based on PriorityQueue.

      • IndexedPriorityQueue

        public IndexedPriorityQueue(T[] objects,
                            java.util.Comparator<? super T> comparator)
        Constructs a priority queue for the given objects. Note that this object runs in linear time and is thus faster than creating an empty queue and adding the items individually.
        Parameters:
        objects - initial objects for the queue
        comparator - comparator deciding on the priority order
